          <h3><a href="/page-07">Investigation Bias</a></h3>
          <p>
            Confirmation bias, selection bias, availability bias, the halo effect, and the bandwagon effect are some of the biases that OSINT investigators should be aware of. To combat these biases, one can use decision-making logs, peer review, work as a team, experiment with different tools and methods, and ensure transparency in their investigations. It is essential to weigh elements that support and contradict the conclusion and be open to criticism to review one's own work.
